clinical_study.brief_title: An Extension Study of V203-AD Study to Evaluate the Safety, Tolerability, Immunogenicity, and Efficacy of UB-311
clinical_study.official_title: An Extension Study of a Phase IIa Study in Patients With Mild Alzheimer's Disease to Evaluate the Safety, Tolerability, Immunogenicity, and Efficacy of UBITh® AD Immunotherapeutic Vaccine (UB-311)

brief_summary.textblock: To evaluate the long-term safety, tolerability and potential efficacy, patients who previously participated in V203-AD study (NCT02551809) will be eligible to participate in the extension study and will receive 3 or 5 doses of UB-311 within a 96-week treatment period followed by a 12-week follow-up period.

clinical_study.why_stopped: United Neuroscience has decided to terminate V203-AD-EXT study based on a treatment assignment error

study_design_info.masking: Quadruple (Participant, Care Provider, Investigator, Outcomes Assessor)

primary_outcome.measure: The Incidence of Adverse Event (AE)/Serious Adverse Event (SAE) [Safety and Tolerability]).
primary_outcome.time_frame: Overall Study Duration/Early Termination, over an average study duration of 326 days
primary_outcome.description: Summary of Treatment Emergent Adverse Events (TEAEs), based on reported adverse events and other safety information including local tolerability at injection site, MRI, vital signs, physical examination, 12-lead ECG and laboratory tests.

primary_outcome.measure: Change From Baseline and Through to the End of the Study in Anti-Aβ Antibody Titers [The Immunogenicity of UB-311]
primary_outcome.time_frame: Overall Study Duration/Early Termination, over an average study duration of 326 days
primary_outcome.description: For the immunogenicity assessment of the investigational product, UB-311, the level of anti-Aβ antibodies in the serum samples will be measured by a validated enzyme immunoassay manufactured by United Biomedical, Inc. (UBI). The level of anti-Aβ antibodies is assessed at every visit throughout the study period.

other_outcome.measure: Change From Baseline and Through to the End of the Study in Alzheimer's Disease Assessment Scale-Cognitive Subscale (ADAS-Cog);
other_outcome.time_frame: Overall Study Duration/Early Termination, over an average study duration of 326 days
other_outcome.description: The ADAS-Cog 13 contains 13 items, with a total scoring range of 0 - 85 and higher scores indicating greater dysfunction. ADAS-Cog scores were evaluated at V1 and V8/ET. The observed values and change from baseline for ADAS-Cog scores by treatment groups in the extension study are presented

other_outcome.measure: Change From Baseline and Through to the End of the Study in Mini-Mental State Exam (MMSE)
other_outcome.time_frame: Overall Study Duration/Early Termination, over an average study duration of 326 days
other_outcome.description: The MMSE is a 30-point questionnaire. The total score range is 0 - 30 and lower scores indicating greater impairment. MMSE scores were evaluated at V1 and V8/ET. The observed values and change from baseline for MMSE scores by treatment groups in the extension study are presented

other_outcome.measure: Change From Baseline and Through to the End of the Study in Clinical Dementia Rating - Sum of Boxes (CDR-SB)
other_outcome.time_frame: Overall Study Duration/Early Termination, over an average study duration of 326 days
other_outcome.description: The CDR-SB includes 6 domains (0 - 3 points/domain), with a total scoring range of 0 - 18 and higher scores indicate greater impartment. CDR-SB scores were evaluated at V1 and V8/ET. The observed values and change from baseline for CDR-SB scores by treatment groups in the extension study are presented

arm_group.description: Subjects will receive 3 doses of UB-311 and 2 doses of placebo.
Subjects will receive 5 doses of UB-311.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Patients who participated in V203-AD trial without major safety concerns;
- Stable doses of permitted medications for 3 months before screening;
- With a caregiver;
- Other inclusion criteria apply
Exclusion Criteria:
- Clinically significant neurological disease other than Alzheimer's disease
- Major psychiatric disorder
- Severe systemic disease
- Serious adverse reactions to any vaccine
- Other exclusion criteria apply

link.description: Site-specific UBITh amyloid-beta vaccine for immunotherapy of Alzheimer's disease.
UB-311, a novel UBITh® amyloid β peptide vaccine for mild Alzheimer's disease.

measure.title: Mini-Mental State Examination
measure.description: MMSE Total Score Presented. The MMSE is a 30-point questionnaire used extensively in clinical and research settings to measure cognitive impairment and is commonly used in medicine and allied health to screen for dementia. It is also used to estimate the severity and progression of cognitive impairment and to follow the course of cognitive changes in an individual over time; thus making it an effective way to document a participant's response to treatment. The total score range is 0 - 30 and lower scores indicating greater impairment.

certain_agreements.pi_employee: Principal Investigators are NOT employed by the organization sponsoring the study.
certain_agreements.restrictive_agreement: Site PIs must jointly publish results, unless permission is granted by Sponsor. If a joint publication is not done within 12 months after trial completion and database lock, then the site may publish its own results; provided that, a) Sponsor has 45 business days to review the proposed publication; b) the PI must delete any confidential information identified by Sponsor; and c) the PI must delay disclosure for 1 year if a patent application is filed by Sponsor.

clinical_results.limitations_and_caveats: 1. Due to the incorrect treatment assignment and study early termination, this study was underpowered for analysis with secondary endpoints. Therefore, all secondary endpoints (change in ADAS-Cog, MMSE, CDR-SB) were considered as exploratory efficacy endpoints. 2. qEEG, cortical thickness, computerized cognitive tests, and the change of amyloid deposition with substantial amount of missing data/visit so they were omitted from group comparison analysis.
